MRP Elgin Initial Reactive Rate Schedule

record_data.record_plain_text:
MRP ELGIN LLC
REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION SOURCES SERVICE
MRP Elgin LLC (“Seller”) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service (“Reactive Supply Service”) from a facility located in Elgin, Illinois (the “Elgin Facility”) in the Commonwealth Edison zone in the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (“PJM”) transmission footprint. This tariff sets forth Seller’s revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Supply Service from the Elgin Facility pursuant to the Reactive Power Revenue Requirements in Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
Seller’s revenue requirement for the Elgin Facility shall be calculated as follows:
Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement is: $700,000.08
Monthly Revenue Requirement is: $58,333.34 (based on Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement divided by 12)
Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the annual charge specified above and shall be effective on the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
